"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The function get_active_figure() is designed to return the current active figure, but it does not check if the figure is actually active before trying to add text to it. The ax.text() call on line 18 will fail if there is no active figure, as it will attempt to add text to a non-existent axes object.\", \"patch\": \"18a19\\n>     ax = ac_fig.axes[0] if ac_fig.axes else None\\n>     if ax is not None:\\n\"}"